1244 (yytext_ptr) = &YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[0];
1245
1246 return ret_val;
1247}

1249/* yy_get_previous_state - get the state just before the EOB char was reached */
1250
1251 static yy_state_type yy_get_previous_state (void)
1252{
1253 yy_state_type yy_current_state;
1254 char *yy_cp;
1255
1256 yy_current_state = (yy_start);
1257
1258 for ( yy_cp = (yytext_ptr) + YY_MORE_ADJ; yy_cp < (yy_c_buf_p); ++yy_cp )
1259 {
1260 YY_CHAR yy_c = (*yy_cp ? yy_ec[YY_SC_TO_UI(*yy_cp)] : 1);
1261 if ( yy_accept[yy_current_state] )
1262 {
1263 (yy_last_accepting_state) = yy_current_state;
1264 (yy_last_accepting_cpos) = yy_cp;
1265 }
1266 while ( yy_chk[yy_base[yy_current_state] + yy_c] != yy_current_state )
1267 {
1268 yy_current_state = (int) yy_def[yy_current_state];
1269 if ( yy_current_state >= 27 )
1270 yy_c = yy_meta[yy_c];
1271 }
1272 yy_current_state = yy_nxt[yy_base[yy_current_state] + yy_c];
1273 }
1274
1275 return yy_current_state;
1276}

1278/* yy_try_NUL_trans - try to make a transition on the NUL character
1279 *
1280 * synopsis
1281 * next_state = yy_try_NUL_trans( current_state );
1282 */
1283 static yy_state_type yy_try_NUL_trans (yy_state_type yy_current_state )
1284{
1285 int yy_is_jam;
1286 char *yy_cp = (yy_c_buf_p);
1287
1288 YY_CHAR yy_c = 1;
1289 if ( yy_accept[yy_current_state] )
1290 {
1291 (yy_last_accepting_state) = yy_current_state;
1292 (yy_last_accepting_cpos) = yy_cp;
1293 }
1294 while ( yy_chk[yy_base[yy_current_state] + yy_c] != yy_current_state )
1295 {
1296 yy_current_state = (int) yy_def[yy_current_state];
1297 if ( yy_current_state >= 27 )
1298 yy_c = yy_meta[yy_c];
1299 }
1300 yy_current_state = yy_nxt[yy_base[yy_current_state] + yy_c];
1301 yy_is_jam = (yy_current_state == 26);
1302
1303 return yy_is_jam ? 0 : yy_current_state;
1304}

1308 static void yyunput (int c, char * yy_bp )
1309{
1310 char *yy_cp;
1311
1312 yy_cp = (yy_c_buf_p);
1313
1314 /* undo effects of setting up yytext */
1315 *yy_cp = (yy_hold_char);
1316
1317 if ( yy_cp < YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf + 2 )
1318 { /* need to shift things up to make room */
1319 /* +2 for EOB chars. */
1320 yy_size_t number_to_move = (yy_n_chars) + 2;
1321 char *dest = &YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[
1322 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size + 2];
1323 char *source =
1324 &YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[number_to_move];
1325
1326 while ( source > YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf )
1327 *--dest = *--source;
1328
1329 yy_cp += (int) (dest - source);
1330 yy_bp += (int) (dest - source);
1331 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars =
1332 (yy_n_chars) = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size;
1333
1334 if ( yy_cp < YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf + 2 )
1335 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "flex scanner push-back overflow" );
1336 }
1337
1338 *--yy_cp = (char) c;
1339
1340 (yytext_ptr) = yy_bp;
1341 (yy_hold_char) = *yy_cp;
1342 (yy_c_buf_p) = yy_cp;
1343}

1347#ifndef YY_NO_INPUT
1348#ifdef __cplusplus
1349 static int yyinput (void)
1350#else
1351 static int input (void)
1352#endif
1353
1354{
1355 int c;
1356
1357 *(yy_c_buf_p) = (yy_hold_char);
1358
1359 if ( *(yy_c_buf_p) == YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR )
1360 {
1361 /* yy_c_buf_p now points to the character we want to return.
1362 * If this occurs *before* the EOB characters, then it's a
1363 * valid NUL; if not, then we've hit the end of the buffer.
1364 */
1365 if ( (yy_c_buf_p) < &YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[(yy_n_chars)] )
1366 /* This was really a NUL. */
1367 *(yy_c_buf_p) = '\0';
1368
1369 else
1370 { /* need more input */
1371 yy_size_t offset = (int) ((yy_c_buf_p) - (yytext_ptr));
1372 ++(yy_c_buf_p);
1373
1374 switch ( yy_get_next_buffer( ) )
1375 {
1376 case EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH:
1377 /* This happens because yy_g_n_b()
1378 * sees that we've accumulated a
1379 * token and flags that we need to
1380 * try matching the token before
1381 * proceeding. But for input(),
1382 * there's no matching to consider.
1383 * So convert the EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH
1384 * to EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE.
1385 */
1386
1387 /* Reset buffer status. */
1388 yyrestart( yyin );
1389
1390 /*FALLTHROUGH*/
1391
1392 case EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE:
1393 {
1394 if ( yywrap( ) )
1395 return 0;
1396
1397 if ( ! (yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof) )
1398 YY_NEW_FILE;
1399#ifdef __cplusplus
1400 return yyinput();
1401#else
1402 return input();
1403#endif
1404 }
1405
1406 case EOB_ACT_CONTINUE_SCAN:
1407 (yy_c_buf_p) = (yytext_ptr) + offset;
1408 break;
1409 }
1410 }
1411 }
1412
1413 c = *(unsigned char *) (yy_c_buf_p); /* cast for 8-bit char's */
1414 *(yy_c_buf_p) = '\0'; /* preserve yytext */
1415 (yy_hold_char) = *++(yy_c_buf_p);
1416
1417 return c;
1418}

1423 *

1425 */

1439/** Switch to a different input buffer.
1440 * @param new_buffer The new input buffer.
1441 *
1442 */
1443 void yy_switch_to_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE new_buffer )
1444{
1445
1446 /* TODO. We should be able to replace this entire function body
1447 * with
1448 * yypop_buffer_state();
1449 * yypush_buffer_state(new_buffer);
1450 */
1451 yyensure_buffer_stack ();
1452 if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER == new_buffer )
1453 return;
1454
1455 if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER )
1456 {
1457 /* Flush out information for old buffer. */
1458 *(yy_c_buf_p) = (yy_hold_char);
1459 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_pos = (yy_c_buf_p);
1460 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = (yy_n_chars);
1461 }
1462
1463 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = new_buffer;
1464 yy_load_buffer_state( );
1465
1466 /* We don't actually know whether we did this switch during
1467 * EOF (yywrap()) processing, but the only time this flag
1468 * is looked at is after yywrap() is called, so it's safe
1469 * to go ahead and always set it.
1470 */
1471 (yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof) = 1;
1472}

1474static void yy_load_buffer_state (void)
1475{
1476 (yy_n_chars) = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars;
1477 (yytext_ptr) = (yy_c_buf_p) = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_pos;
1478 yyin = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_input_file;
1479 (yy_hold_char) = *(yy_c_buf_p);
1480}

1482/** Allocate and initialize an input buffer state.
1483 * @param file A readable stream.
1484 * @param size The character buffer size in bytes. When in doubt, use @c YY_BUF_SIZE.
1485 *
1486 * @return the allocated buffer state.
1487 */
1488 YY_BUFFER_STATE yy_create_buffer (FILE * file, yy_size_t size )
1489{
1490 YY_BUFFER_STATE b;
1491
1492 b = (YY_BUFFER_STATE) yyalloc( sizeof( struct yy_buffer_state ) );
1493 if ( ! b )
1494 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_create_buffer()" );
1495
1496 b->yy_buf_size = size;
1497
1498 /* yy_ch_buf has to be 2 characters longer than the size given because
1499 * we need to put in 2 end-of-buffer characters.
1500 */
1501 b->yy_ch_buf = (char *) yyalloc( (yy_size_t) (b->yy_buf_size + 2) );
1502 if ( ! b->yy_ch_buf )
1503 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_create_buffer()" );
1504
1505 b->yy_is_our_buffer = 1;
1506
1507 yy_init_buffer( b, file );
1508
1509 return b;
1510}

1512/** Destroy the buffer.
1513 * @param b a buffer created with yy_create_buffer()
1514 *
1515 */
1516 void yy_delete_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE b )
1517{
1518
1519 if ( ! b )
1520 return;
1521
1522 if ( b == YY_CURRENT_BUFFER ) /* Not sure if we should pop here. */
1523 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = (YY_BUFFER_STATE) 0;
1524
1525 if ( b->yy_is_our_buffer )
1526 yyfree( (void *) b->yy_ch_buf );
1527
1528 yyfree( (void *) b );
1529}

1531/* Initializes or reinitializes a buffer.
1532 * This function is sometimes called more than once on the same buffer,
1533 * such as during a yyrestart() or at EOF.
1534 */
1535 static void yy_init_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE b, FILE * file )
1536
1537{
1538 int oerrno = errno;
1539
1540 yy_flush_buffer( b );
1541
1542 b->yy_input_file = file;
1543 b->yy_fill_buffer = 1;
1544
1545 /* If b is the current buffer, then yy_init_buffer was _probably_
1546 * called from yyrestart() or through yy_get_next_buffer.
1547 * In that case, we don't want to reset the lineno or column.
1548 */
1549 if (b != YY_CURRENT_BUFFER){
1550 b->yy_bs_lineno = 1;
1551 b->yy_bs_column = 0;
1552 }
1553
1554 b->yy_is_interactive = file ? (isatty( fileno(file) ) > 0) : 0;
1555
1556 errno = oerrno;
1557}

1559/** Discard all buffered characters. On the next scan, YY_INPUT will be called.
1560 * @param b the buffer state to be flushed, usually @c YY_CURRENT_BUFFER.
1561 *
1562 */
1563 void yy_flush_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE b )
1564{
1565 if ( ! b )
1566 return;
1567
1568 b->yy_n_chars = 0;
1569
1570 /* We always need two end-of-buffer characters. The first causes
1571 * a transition to the end-of-buffer state. The second causes
1572 * a jam in that state.
1573 */
1574 b->yy_ch_buf[0] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
1575 b->yy_ch_buf[1] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
1576
1577 b->yy_buf_pos = &b->yy_ch_buf[0];
1578
1579 b->yy_at_bol = 1;
1580 b->yy_buffer_status = YY_BUFFER_NEW;
1581
1582 if ( b == YY_CURRENT_BUFFER )
1583 yy_load_buffer_state( );
1584}

1586/** Pushes the new state onto the stack. The new state becomes
1587 * the current state. This function will allocate the stack
1588 * if necessary.
1589 * @param new_buffer The new state.
1590 *
1591 */
1592void yypush_buffer_state (YY_BUFFER_STATE new_buffer )
1593{
1594 if (new_buffer == NULL)
1595 return;
1596
1597 yyensure_buffer_stack();
1598
1599 /* This block is copied from yy_switch_to_buffer. */
1600 if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER )
1601 {
1602 /* Flush out information for old buffer. */
1603 *(yy_c_buf_p) = (yy_hold_char);
1604 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_pos = (yy_c_buf_p);
1605 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = (yy_n_chars);
1606 }
1607
1608 /* Only push if top exists. Otherwise, replace top. */
1609 if (YY_CURRENT_BUFFER)
1610 (yy_buffer_stack_top)++;
1611 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = new_buffer;
1612
1613 /* copied from yy_switch_to_buffer. */
1614 yy_load_buffer_state( );
1615 (yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof) = 1;
1616}
1617
1618/** Removes and deletes the top of the stack, if present.
1619 * The next element becomes the new top.
1620 *
1621 */
1622void yypop_buffer_state (void)
1623{
1624 if (!YY_CURRENT_BUFFER)
1625 return;
1626
1627 yy_delete_buffer(YY_CURRENT_BUFFER );
1628 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = NULL;
1629 if ((yy_buffer_stack_top) > 0)
1630 --(yy_buffer_stack_top);
1631
1632 if (YY_CURRENT_BUFFER) {
1633 yy_load_buffer_state( );
1634 (yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof) = 1;
1635 }
1636}

1638/* Allocates the stack if it does not exist.
1639 * Guarantees space for at least one push.
1640 */
1641static void yyensure_buffer_stack (void)
1642{
1643 yy_size_t num_to_alloc;
1644
1645 if (!(yy_buffer_stack)) {
1646
1647 /* First allocation is just for 2 elements, since we don't know if this
1648 * scanner will even need a stack. We use 2 instead of 1 to avoid an
1649 * immediate realloc on the next call.
1650 */
1651 num_to_alloc = 1; /* After all that talk, this was set to 1 anyways... */
1652 (yy_buffer_stack) = (struct yy_buffer_state**)yyalloc
1653 (num_to_alloc * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*)
1654 );
1655 if ( ! (yy_buffer_stack) )
1656 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yyensure_buffer_stack()" );
1657
1658 memset((yy_buffer_stack), 0, num_to_alloc * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*));
1659
1660 (yy_buffer_stack_max) = num_to_alloc;
1661 (yy_buffer_stack_top) = 0;
1662 return;
1663 }
1664
1665 if ((yy_buffer_stack_top) >= ((yy_buffer_stack_max)) - 1){
1666
1667 /* Increase the buffer to prepare for a possible push. */
1668 yy_size_t grow_size = 8 /* arbitrary grow size */;
1669
1670 num_to_alloc = (yy_buffer_stack_max) + grow_size;
1671 (yy_buffer_stack) = (struct yy_buffer_state**)yyrealloc
1672 ((yy_buffer_stack),
1673 num_to_alloc * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*)
1674 );
1675 if ( ! (yy_buffer_stack) )
1676 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yyensure_buffer_stack()" );
1677
1678 /* zero only the new slots.*/
1679 memset((yy_buffer_stack) + (yy_buffer_stack_max), 0, grow_size * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*));
1680 (yy_buffer_stack_max) = num_to_alloc;
1681 }
1682}

1684/** Setup the input buffer state to scan directly from a user-specified character buffer.
1685 * @param base the character buffer
1686 * @param size the size in bytes of the character buffer
1687 *
1688 * @return the newly allocated buffer state object.
1689 */
1690YY_BUFFER_STATE yy_scan_buffer (char * base, yy_size_t size )
1691{
1692 YY_BUFFER_STATE b;
1693
1694 if ( size < 2 ||
1695 base[size-2] != YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR ||
1696 base[size-1] != YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR )
1697 /* They forgot to leave room for the EOB's. */
1698 return NULL;
1699
1700 b = (YY_BUFFER_STATE) yyalloc( sizeof( struct yy_buffer_state ) );
1701 if ( ! b )
1702 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_scan_buffer()" );
1703
1704 b->yy_buf_size = (size - 2); /* "- 2" to take care of EOB's */
1705 b->yy_buf_pos = b->yy_ch_buf = base;
1706 b->yy_is_our_buffer = 0;
1707 b->yy_input_file = NULL;
1708 b->yy_n_chars = b->yy_buf_size;
1709 b->yy_is_interactive = 0;
1710 b->yy_at_bol = 1;
1711 b->yy_fill_buffer = 0;
1712 b->yy_buffer_status = YY_BUFFER_NEW;
1713
1714 yy_switch_to_buffer( b );
1715
1716 return b;
1717}

1733/** Setup the input buffer state to scan the given bytes. The next call to yylex() will
1734 * scan from a @e copy of @a bytes.
1735 * @param yybytes the byte buffer to scan
1736 * @param _yybytes_len the number of bytes in the buffer pointed to by @a bytes.
1737 *
1738 * @return the newly allocated buffer state object.
1739 */
1740YY_BUFFER_STATE yy_scan_bytes (const char * yybytes, yy_size_t _yybytes_len )
1741{
1742 YY_BUFFER_STATE b;
1743 char *buf;
1744 yy_size_t n;
1745 yy_size_t i;
1746
1747 /* Get memory for full buffer, including space for trailing EOB's. */
1748 n = (yy_size_t) (_yybytes_len + 2);
1749 buf = (char *) yyalloc( n );
1750 if ( ! buf )
1751 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_scan_bytes()" );
1752
1753 for ( i = 0; i < _yybytes_len; ++i )
1754 buf[i] = yybytes[i];
1755
1756 buf[_yybytes_len] = buf[_yybytes_len+1] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
1757
1758 b = yy_scan_buffer( buf, n );
1759 if ( ! b )
1760 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "bad buffer in yy_scan_bytes()" );
1761
1762 /* It's okay to grow etc. this buffer, and we should throw it
1763 * away when we're done.
1764 */
1765 b->yy_is_our_buffer = 1;
1766
1767 return b;
1768}

1905/* yylex_destroy is for both reentrant and non-reentrant scanners. */
1906int yylex_destroy (void)
1907{
1908
1909 /* Pop the buffer stack, destroying each element. */
1910 while(YY_CURRENT_BUFFER){
1911 yy_delete_buffer( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER );
1912 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = NULL;
1913 yypop_buffer_state();
1914 }
1915
1916 /* Destroy the stack itself. */
1917 yyfree((yy_buffer_stack) );

2020int next_item(nstate)
2021int nstate;
2022{
2023 struct lwordtab *wt;
2024
2025 if (opts & OPT_DEBUG)
2026 printf("text=[%s] id=%d next=%d\n", yytext, nstate, next);
2027 if (next == IL_TOKEN) {
2028 next = -1;
2029 return save_token();
2030 }
2031 token++;
2032
2033 for (wt = words; wt->word; wt++)
2034 if (!strcasecmp(wt->word, (char *)yytext))
2035 return next_state(wt->state, wt->next);
2036 if (opts & OPT_DEBUG)
2037 printf("unknown keyword=[%s]\n", yytext);
2038 next = -1;
2039 if (nstate == IL_NUMBER)

2046int next_state(nstate, fornext)
2047int nstate, fornext;
2048{
2049 next = fornext;
2050
2051 switch (nstate)
2052 {
2053 case IL_IPV4 :
2054 case IL_TCP :
2055 case IL_UDP :
2056 case IL_ICMP :
2057 case IL_DATA :
2058 case IL_INTERFACE :
2059 case IL_ARP :
2060 oldipproto = ipproto;
2061 ipproto = nstate;
2062 break;
2063 case IL_SUM :
2064 if (ipproto == IL_IPV4)
2065 nstate = IL_V4SUM;
2066 else if (ipproto == IL_TCP)
2067 nstate = IL_TCPSUM;
2068 else if (ipproto == IL_UDP)
2069 nstate = IL_UDPSUM;
2070 break;
2071 case IL_OPT :
2072 if (ipproto == IL_IPV4)
2073 nstate = IL_V4OPT;
2074 else if (ipproto == IL_TCP)
2075 nstate = IL_TCPOPT;
2076 break;
2077 case IL_IPO_NOP :
2078 if (ipproto == IL_TCP)
2079 nstate = IL_TCPO_NOP;
2080 break;
2081 case IL_IPO_EOL :
2082 if (ipproto == IL_TCP)
2083 nstate = IL_TCPO_EOL;
2084 break;
2085 case IL_IPO_TS :
2086 if (ipproto == IL_TCP)
2087 nstate = IL_TCPO_TS;
2088 break;
2089 case IL_OFF :
2090 if (ipproto == IL_IPV4)
2091 nstate = IL_V4OFF;
2092 else if (ipproto == IL_TCP)
2093 nstate = IL_TCPOFF;
2094 break;
2095 case IL_LEN :
2096 if (ipproto == IL_IPV4)
2097 nstate = IL_V4LEN;
2098 else if (ipproto == IL_UDP)
2099 nstate = IL_UDPLEN;
2100 break;
2101 }
2102 return nstate;
